  "texts": [
    "The cluster consist of deep learning algorithm terms like long shot term memory, convolutional neural network, deep learning model, neural network, neural topic model, clustering and word embedding useful to perform TM for natural language processing tasks (such as information retrieval systems, topic classification, multi-label classification, text summarisation, and text classification as shown in the co-occurrence map).",
    "• As shown in Fig. 13 (in appendix), terms in cluster 5 suggest the cluster can be profiled as \"Software\".",
    "This is because the cluster consist of terms like open systems, opensource software, software design, stack overflow, bug reports, codes, software engineering, open-source systems.",
    "Overall, the keywords co-occurrence produced 5 clusters profiled as applications and algorithms (cluster 1), information mining (cluster 2), review analysis, data source, sentiment analysis and public health (cluster 3), natural language processing (cluster 4), and software (cluster 5).",
    "These themes indicate the author and index keywords, of which the review analysis, data source (social media, questionnaire, and electronic health records), sentiment analysis and public health (cluster 3) are the most recent research keyword trend."
